11.1 Viz: Attempt 1

Codene_countries(returnclass = "sf") |&gt;
  select(name, geometry) |&gt;
  left_join(fc |&gt; select(-co2_emmission),
            join_by(name == country)) |&gt;
  ggplot() +
  geom_sf(aes(fill = consumption)) +
  facet_wrap(~food_category) +
  theme(legend.position = "bottom")







What problems does the above visualization suffer? - Unclear or meaningless NA facet. - The shading is very dark for most countries across facets, making hard to distinguish differences in consumption - There are no country borders, making harder to distinguish regions - Some countries are missing, posible because when joining data sets, the names were different spelled.

11.2 Viz: Attempt 2

Codene_countries(returnclass = "sf") |&gt;
  select(name, geometry) |&gt;
  mutate(name = ifelse(name == "United States of America", "USA", name)) |&gt;
  mutate(name = ifelse(name == "Bosnia and Herz.", "Bosnia and Herzegovina", name)) |&gt;
  mutate(name = ifelse(name == "Czechia", "Czech Republic", name)) |&gt;
  mutate(name = ifelse(name == "Taiwan", "Taiwan. ROC", name)) |&gt;
  left_join(fc |&gt; select(-co2_emmission),
            join_by(name == country)) |&gt;
  pivot_wider(names_from = food_category,
              values_from = consumption) |&gt;
  select(-"NA") |&gt;
  pivot_longer(cols = c(-name, -geometry),
               names_to = "food_category",
               values_to = "consumption") |&gt;
  ggplot() +
  geom_sf(aes(fill = consumption)) +
  facet_wrap(~food_category) +
  theme(legend.position = "bottom")







What problems does the above visualization suffer? - The color palette doesn’t differentiate well between low and high consumption. It is also no inclusive for colorblind viewers. - There are no countries labels or border lines. - Many small maps are hard to read and compared.

11.3 Viz: Attempt 3

Codene_countries(returnclass = "sf") |&gt;
  select(name, geometry) |&gt;
  mutate(name = ifelse(name == "United States of America", "USA", name)) |&gt;
  mutate(name = ifelse(name == "Bosnia and Herz.", "Bosnia and Herzegovina", name)) |&gt;
  mutate(name = ifelse(name == "Czechia", "Czech Republic", name)) |&gt;
  mutate(name = ifelse(name == "Taiwan", "Taiwan. ROC", name)) |&gt;
  left_join(
    fc |&gt; 
      select(-co2_emmission) |&gt;
      group_by(food_category) |&gt;
      mutate(consumption = (consumption - mean(consumption))/sd(consumption)),
      join_by(name == country)) |&gt;
  pivot_wider(names_from = food_category, values_from = consumption) |&gt;
  select(-"NA") |&gt;
  pivot_longer(cols = c(-name, -geometry),
               names_to = "food_category",
               values_to = "consumption") |&gt;
  ggplot() +
  geom_sf(aes(fill = consumption)) +
  facet_wrap(~food_category) +
  theme(legend.position = "bottom")







How can the visualization be enhanced? - Color scale improvements - Small countries can be hard to see on a world map - Countries outlines/borders could help visualization
